scoringmanagement

Class Score

  • java.lang.Object
    • scoringmanagement.Score

  • public class Score
extends java.lang.Object
    Companion class to Scorer. Places the values Scorer writes into an object and stores it for further manipulation if required. studentScores array holds the score defined as (output correct/ output incorrect)*30+10(compiles)+10(executes)=possible total of 50 pnts. A seperate array stores unscored aspects of the program with data only as feedback for the client. Example format: studentScores array labData array ------------------------ ---------------------------------- 20 | False | True | | 56 | 5 | 2 | 5 | ------------------------ ---------------------------------- Score--Compiled?-Runs? #comments-#JavaDocs-#Break-#return
    Version:
    5/31
    Author:
    Darshan & Max
